  "rationale": "<p>Rewrite the right side using a fractional exponent: <sup>9</sup>&radic;(5<sup>4</sup>) = 5<sup>4/9</sup>. The equation becomes 5<sup>6<i>c</i></sup> = 5<sup>4/9</sup>, so 6<i>c</i> = 4/9. Dividing both sides by 6 gives <i>c</i> = 4/54 = 2/27.</p>",
